### Test LuhaRide Authentication API
### Use REST Client extension in VS Code or copy to Postman

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:3000/health

### 2. Send OTP (New User Registration)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "purpose": "registration"
}

### 3. Verify OTP and Register (Use OTP from console)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "otp": "123456",
  "name": "Test User",
  "role": "passenger"
}

### 4. Get Current User (Use accessToken from step 3)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Update Profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### 6. Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 7. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 8. Send OTP for Login (Existing User)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "purpose": "login"
}

### 9. Verify OTP and Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "otp": "123456"
}
